---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Releases | OpenInterstate">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <p class="kicker">Releases</p>
    <h1>Dated, documented, and checksummed.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Public releases are the primary product surface. The first release is not published yet,
      but the release contract and manifest structure are already defined.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <p class="kicker">Latest</p>
        <h3>Not published yet</h3>
        <p>The project is in bootstrap phase. The first release will appear here with checksums and schema metadata.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <p class="kicker">Formats</p>
        <h3>GeoParquet first</h3>
        <p>Reference routes and small examples will be published in secondary formats.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <p class="kicker">Contract</p>
        <h3>Manifest + schema version</h3>
        <p>The release manifest defines the machine-readable release surface.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
